N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 19 ยง 332.5 - Alphabetical arrangement in register

State Regulations

The name of each military voter and his residence address
shall be entered in the alphabetically arranged register or on the registration
records of his home election district, and his military address and/or his
mailing address or other data shall be entered in the final column or
registration remarks column or space, except as may hereafter be determined by
the directors pursuant to subdivision 2 of section 305 of the Election

Law. Notes
